#)What is Bean Scope?
Most common:

singleton (default)
prototype

Short answer:
“Bean scope defines how many instances of a bean Spring creates.”
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#)13. What is the difference between Singleton and Prototype scope?
“Singleton → one bean instance per application
Prototype → new instance each time it’s requested.”

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#) What is AOP (Aspect-Oriented Programming)?
“AOP allows adding cross-cutting concerns like logging, security, 
or transactions without modifying business logic.”

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Problem AOP Solves
In traditional programming, you would have to write logging code inside nearly every single one of your core functions.
 This makes the code messy, harder to read, and difficult to change later 
 (if you decide to use a different logging system, you have to edit hundreds of files).


-------------------------------------------------------
#)What is the purpose of application.yml vs application.properties?
#)Both application.yml and application.properties serve the same purpose in Spring Boot:
➡ They are used to store application configuration
(e.g., server port, database config, logging, profiles, actuator, etc.)
The difference is only in format, not functionality.

